(Alemeno Marker Scanner - Approach) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
() Tj
T*
(Marker choice) Tj
T*
(The app uses the provided Marker 1. It is a square black border with a single filled) Tj
T*
(black finder block near the top-left corner. The remaining interior is mostly empty,) Tj
T*
(which leaves room for encoded content and makes the marker easy to distinguish from) Tj
T*
(ordinary square objects.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Camera flow) Tj
T*
(The React Native app renders a live back-camera preview with a 1:1 capture ratio. On) Tj
T*
(supported Android devices it selects a square picture size between 2000x2000 and) Tj
T*
(3000x3000 pixels, preferring the size closest to 2500x2500. The scan loop captures up to) Tj
T*
(60 frames and stops once 20 valid marker crops are produced.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Detection) Tj
T*
(Each JPEG frame is decoded in JavaScript, thresholded for true black pixels, and scanned) Tj
T*
(for the largest square-like connected component. The detector extracts the four extreme) Tj
T*
(corners of that component, validates that all four outer edges are continuous, and) Tj
T*
(perspective-warps the candidate into a 300x300 image.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Orientation correction) Tj
T*
(After warping, the detector measures four corner finder zones. The crop is rotated in) Tj
T*
(90-degree steps until the filled finder block is in the top-left location. The final) Tj
T*
(image is encoded as JPEG and displayed exactly at 300x300 pixels.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(False-positive rejection) Tj
T*
(Validation checks the four black border bands, the expected top-left finder block, the) Tj
T*
(absence of finder blocks in the other corners, low central black density, and the red) Tj
T*
(error mark used in the supplied incorrect samples. The included test runner verifies) Tj
T*
(that the three correct Marker 1 images are accepted and the four incorrect Marker 1) Tj
T*
(images are rejected.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Performance) Tj
T*
(Candidate detection runs on a downsampled frame for speed. Only the accepted square) Tj
T*
(candidate is warped at 300x300 resolution, keeping per-frame work small enough for the) Tj
T*
(assignment target of a sub-3000 ms scan-to-result path on a typical Android device.) Tj
